<dl id="n09018a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09018a">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09018a"> 18(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">H</font> accused can now (1920) / give evidence</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The materialism (whether conscious or sub-conscious does not matter very much) of the last few generations has led to various results of practical importance, such as sanitation, Marxian socialism, and the <mark>right of an accused person to give evidence</mark> on his or her own behalf. <small> J. B. S. Haldane, <a name="DAED" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DAED"><cite title="source">Dedalus</cite></a> (1923) 14f</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
